parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause fires, electrical shocks, and loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: fires starting from the passenger side headlight
lights turning on and off without prompting
electrical windows and seat adjustments not responding.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Software Issues with Advanced Safety Features
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of advanced safety features, such as the Collision Mitigation Braking System (CMBS), can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: CMBS warning light comes on permanently
indicating that the driver should apply brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The battery drain and electrical failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Battery needs to be replaced multiple times
lights turning on and off without prompting
car doesn't turn over with proper key usage

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the HandsFreeLink Bluetooth system can cause battery drain, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: HandsFreeLink Bluetooth system doesn't turn off
cars stopping mid-road due to no power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the air conditioning system can cause strong fumes to emit inside the vehicle, making it uncomfortable to breathe and potentially causing health problems.
symptoms: Strong smell of fumes inside the vehicle
fumes sensed not only while driving but also while waiting for a light to change.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the infotainment system can cause distraction while driving, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Back-up camera video/navigation module and stereo/clock screens remain blank
not showing correct time and Bluetooth connection status.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Excessive Oil Consumption due to Piston Defect
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive oil consumption can lead to engine damage, overheating, and potentially cause the engine to seize, resulting in a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
The engine stalling and lockup can cause the vehicle to lose power and control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: steering wheel and brakes lock up
no warning lamps or codes on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The torque converter failure can cause the vehicle to lose power and control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
The engine failure and stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power and control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
Excessive oil consumption can lead to premature engine wear, engine failure, and potentially cause accidents due to engine stalling or loss of power.
The judder from the torque converter lock-up clutch can cause sudden acceleration, loss of control, and accidents, especially when parking or maneuvering at low speeds.
symptoms: jerking or surging of the vehicle
especially when shifting into park or driving at low speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities, especially when the vehicle is unable to be controlled or stopped.
symptoms: engine remaining on during the incident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Multiple system failures can cause a range of safety issues, including loss of control, accidents, and injuries, as well as decreased vehicle reliability and performance.
symptoms: shaking steering wheel at high speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause the vehicle to veer off course or lose control, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The steering wheel moves upwards independently
the vehicle veers to the left or right while driving
error codes appear on the dashboard related to VSA stability
